/fenye.jpg hieght=285 width=129></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   A Knight comes to rest</span><hr size=1> The frozen winds of the Ice Clad region bit deep into Llannu's exposed cheeks. Her fur coat provided much warmth, but even her little button nose was red from the numbing cold.<br>
The young wood elf was out for a bit of morning exploration. The skies above her still lazily hung in dawn, the sun a white frozen ball in the sky. There wasn't much to see this morning, and she was speeding along the terrain like a wisp out of hell. <br>
The wooden cabin her and her friends shared came into view. A small plume of blackened smoke rose from the hole in the roof, a sign that breakfast was in the making. <br>
<br>
A freezing draft of wind burst into the cabin as Llannu opened the door, but noone shuddered at the cold. Instead, the occupants remained sitting, or standing. <br>
Llannu pulled back the hood of her furry coat, and glanced around the room. There was a single log burning in the firepit, but no meal being cooked over it. Tanari, the oldest of the group, looked up with red eyes of sadness. <br>
In that moment, Llannu's heart welled up to her throaght, as she did not see one member of the group. <br>
Tilana, the large barbarian warrioress, stood firm against the wall, arms crossed over her chest, and her helmet pushed down just enough to cover her eyes.<br>
Daemonael sat on the mattress, her head buried in her arms. Silent sobs snuck out from her curly white locks of hair that draped over the wizard's head and arms.<br>
<br>
&quot;Where is she?&quot; Llannu asked weakly. Looking up at Tanari, who was now standing, she recieved her answer.<br>
&quot;Fenye.. has left us. She won't be coming back, sweety.&quot; Tears welled up in Tanari's eyes, and a knot rose up her throaght, preventing her from speaking further. Llannu's lips quavered for a moment, but after a moment the young bard ran into Tanari's arms, screaming of anguish and denial.<br>
<br>
The two held each other for what seemed like hours, before a knock at the cabin door finally separated the hazy illusion of sorrow from reality. Tilana calmly walked over and opened the door, revealing the cleric who was called for. <br>
&quot;Ma'am I'm sorry.. There is nothing I can do. Her soul will not reunite with her body. It is rare this happens, but when the soul longs for something for so long, and it's needs are not quenched, the soul can leave the body and never return. I'm sorry.. but I can't do anything.&quot;<br>
Tilana merely nodded and paid the cleric his dues, stepped outside, and shut the door quietly behind her.<br>
<br>
The winds were fierce now, but to the tall barbarian, who grew up in the cold lands of the Everfrost Mountains, these winds were no bother. Creepy shadows from a tree that the dawn's sun created stretched out across the yard to the cabin where she stood. At the base of this tree lay the body of one of the greatest heroes Felwithe had ever seen.<br>
Her feet crunched in the wind frozen snow as she made her way over to the sleeping champion.<br>
Her brilliant armor still shone with the majestic blue of a deep ocean, and her sword still gleamed as white as new fallen snow. The sword was clenched tightly in her gauntleted hands, the blade lay between her legs and driven into the snow, supporting the body into a sitting position. Her visor was shut, and only the long golden strands of hair was visible.<br>
A tear rolled off Tilana's cheek, but froze to the corner of her lip. The warrior looked down at her sleeping friend, and remembered all the times they had shared together in life.<br>
Before long, Tanari joined Tilana, with Llannu cradled in her arms, still stiffling a cry now and then. Daemonael strode in, as elegant as any Tier'Dal could be, even in her state of mourning.<br>
The four stood there, remembering times that Fenye had led them. The times that Fenye had grieved with them, and the times that Fenye had cheered them on. <br>
Llannu's face was still buried in Tanari's neck, unwanting to look at Fenye's body, so Tanari had to be strong for both of them.<br>
<br>
Almost as soon as they were ready to go back in and prepare to bury the body, Fenye's hand released the sword. As it fell, the blade kicked up a tiny bit of snow, landing with a ping as the hilt touched her legplate. The armor caved in a little bit, enough to get the attention of the four.<br>
<br>
Tilana stepped forward, lifting the visor, but gasped as thier was no longer a body inside the suit of armor. <br>
Tanari smiled, as the warm winds of the Faydarks passed over and through them, the soft whispers of the Mother soothing thier sadness. <br>
<br>
Kissing sleeping Llannu's forehead, Tanari said under her breath, &quot;I guess it was truely your time to go, my friend. We will all remember you in your greatest form, Fenye.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that, the four adventurers returned to thier cabin, to once again plan new and great adventures. The only sounds were the whispers in the winds, the sounds of a soul joyfully reuniting with the heavens. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usvaboda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Svaboda</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/20/01 12:26:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.users.qwest.net/~tharper1/myweb4/svaface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A Knight comes to rest</span><hr size=1> /cheer Fenye nice! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utanari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Chaos</span><br>  Posts: 499<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/21/01 7:15:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisroleplaying.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A Knight comes to rest</span><hr size=1> /cry /cry /cry<br>
