Tanari left the sleeping Llannu and the others and went out to take care of the funeral. She carried the armor and sword with compassion and grace. As she came to the musoleom, she pushed inside and carefully laid the armor out, making sure to position it properly. Laying Fenye's gleaming, magical sword over her chest and cupping it in her hands, she knelt over her long time companions helmet.<br>
<br>
Kissing the visor softly, she said her goodbyes to the person who meant so much to her, the one that showed her how to be strong and never give up. To never back down from any monster or foul creature.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know you were tired of this world my love, and i will keep my promise to look after your little ones. But do not think you are alone. There are many in this world that will remember you as i do and your strength and shining example will fuel the desire of others to follow in your footsteps as i have.&quot; tanari whispered to her fallen companion.<br>
<br>
Rising from Fenye's helmet, she said will a strong voice and great vehemence, &quot;You were always strong and i tried to follow your example, but i always felt like i would never be your equal. You will not be alone or without me for long. The priests say they cant bring you back, but they dont carry the fires of love in their hearts as I do. I will not give up hope. I will find a way to be with you again, wether that is resurrecting you, or traveling to the planes and facing the gods, i will be with you again. If i have to, i'll make Cazic Thule beg on his hands and knees to give me the power to bring you back. And if i cant, then the sooner i will be with you in the afterlife.&quot;<br>
<br>
Bending down to give one last kiss to the armor that had so inspired her, she backed away toward the door to the crypt. Taking one of her magical daggers from her boot, Tanari sliced open her left palm. Mixing the blood in her hands, she began to speak words of power, as she spoke, the air seemed to shimmer and squirm. Tanari finished the incantation and let out a scream, and as she did, all of the sconces in the crypt burst to life with a fire more bright than any torch. Looking at them, Tanari knew they would never die out, just like the fires in her heart. <br>
<br>
Reaching into her pouch for some other components, she began another spell, this one far more powerful. Over the next few hours, she traced the magical runes all over the crypt, runes made with her own blood. And finishing the spell, she felt a small part of her soul leave her body and reside in the crypt itself. She knew that from this day forward, if anyone or anything tried to disturb her companions tomb, she would magically appear to defend it.<br>
<br>
Finally, opening the door, she turned back to the interior and faced the armor of her friend and teacher. &quot;I will miss you dearly Fenye. You were more than a friend, more than a teacher, you were the fire in my life, the fire that kept me warm during those cold nights, and the fire that kept me going in battle even after far better warriors had already fallen in combat. Til we meet again my love.&quot; Tanari took her huge sword off her back and raised it in salute to her friend. &quot;The world and the gods shall not forget you Fenye! I will make sure of it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Closing the door to the crypt, she started back toward the cabin, but stopped halfway there. Looking back, a well of tears began to fall down her face. Then looking to the sky, she let loose a bellowing cry to the heavens, cursing the gods and all the powers that be. Letting them know that chaos will reign down on the world til she was reunited with her friend.<br>
<br>
Entering the cabin, she saw the looks upon all those within and the terrified look in Llannu's eyes. Tanari bent over the little bard and kissed her forehead. &quot;I must go on a long journey little one. There is something i must do. I will come by from time to time to make sure you are ok. If you need me for anything, send Ambridahl to find me, and i will return like lightning.&quot; Little Llannu looked up at Tanari and smiled..&quot;I know you will. You were always there with her.&quot; <br>
<br>
As Tanari put on her armor and gathered her things, Llannu couldnt stop the temptation to walk up behind Tanari and pinch her butt. With a yelp, Tanari turned around and looked at Llannu. The angry look on her face melted into a silly grin, and she smiled at Llannu. &quot;Thank you little one, i needed that.&quot;<br>
<br>
Walking outside, she hugged everyone and waved goodbye. &quot;I'll return soon and tell you of my journeys. Be safe and look after each other.&quot; Kissing each one goodbye, she turned and began another spell. As her form changed into that of a great wolf, she ran into the distance, howling. Off in the distance, the other villagers could have sworn they heard the word Fenye floating along the breezes.<br>
<br>
<br>
I will miss you Fenye. <br>
<br>
